---
import Container from "@components/container.astro";
import Cta from "@components/cta.astro";
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
import Sectionhead from "@components/sectionhead.astro";
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
---

<Layout
  footerMargin={false}
  title="Financial Operations Review"
  description="A comprehensive diagnostic and strategic roadmap for ecommerce founders. Transform from financial firefighting to scalable systems with our fixed-price operations review."
>
  <Container class="mt-16">
    <Sectionhead>
      <Fragment slot="title">Your Roadmap to a <span
        class="bold text-brand-gold-text block">Scalable Finance Function</span></Fragment>
      <Fragment slot="desc">
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          <p class="text-lg text-content-primary font-bold">Your strategic roadmap to a scalable business. A fixed-price investment for ambitious ecommerce founders who need to stop firefighting and start leading again.</p>
          <p class="text-content-primary mt-4 text-left">As your business grows, it’s easy to feel like you’re patching
            holes in a system that was never designed to handle this level of complexity. You know things could be
            better, more efficient, and more automated, but identifying where to start—and what to prioritise—feels
            impossible. The Financial Operations Review is the definitive first step to regaining control.</p>
        </div>
      </Fragment>
    </Sectionhead>
  </Container>

  <div class="bg-surface-secondary py-16 my-16">
    <Container>
      <Sectionhead>
        <Fragment slot="title">Does This Sound Familiar?</Fragment>
        <Fragment slot="desc">
          <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
            <p class="text-content-primary mt-4 text-left">You're a successful founder, but you're constantly pulled
              into the financial weeds. You're likely experiencing some of these symptoms of operational strain:</p>
            <ul class="grid mt-4 text-left gap-y-4">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-content-primary">
                <Icon name="ph:check-circle-fill" class="w-6 h-6 flex-shrink-0" />

                <span>
                  <b class="block">You're the CEO, acting like a bookkeeper</b>
                  You spend 5-10 hours a week chasing invoices, authorising payments, or trying to reconcile Shopify payouts instead of focusing on strategy and growth
                </span>
              </li>

              <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-content-primary">
                <Icon name="ph:check-circle-fill" class="w-6 h-6 flex-shrink-0" />

                <span>
                  <b class="block">You feel like you're flying blind</b>
                  You want to make a big decision about the future direction of your company, such as expanding to a new market, or bringing fulfilment in-house to meet increase demand, but you don't fully trust your numbers to reveal your true, real-time profitability. Big decisions feel like guesswork
                </span>
              </li>

              <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-content-primary">
                <Icon name="ph:check-circle-fill" class="w-6 h-6 flex-shrink-0" />

                <span>
                  <b class="block">Your finance team is drowning</b>
                  Month-end takes ten days, not two. You're considering hiring another person just to keep up with the sheer volume of manual data entry and reconciliation
                </span>
              </li>

              <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-content-primary">
                <Icon name="ph:check-circle-fill" class="w-6 h-6 flex-shrink-0" />

                <span>
                  <b class="block">Costly mistakes are starting to creep in</b>
                  You've had near-misses with duplicate supplier payments, damaged relationships by paying late, or you have a nagging feeling your VAT claims aren't as accurate as they should be
                </span>
              </li>

            </ul>
          </div>
        </Fragment>
      </Sectionhead>
    </Container>
  </div>

  <Container>
    <Sectionhead>
      <Fragment slot="title">Our Four-Step Diagnostic Process</Fragment>
      <Fragment slot="desc">
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          <p class="text-content-primary text-left">Before you can build, you need a blueprint. Our Review is a comprehensive diagnostic of your entire financial workflow—from sales and stock to payments and reporting. We provide an objective, expert view of what’s working, what’s broken, and what’s about to break.</p>
          <ul class="grid mt-4 text-left gap-y-4">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-content-primary">
              <Icon name="ph:number-circle-one" class="w-7 h-7 flex-shrink-0" />

              <span>
                <b class="block">The Deep Dive Discovery</b>
                We start by listening. In confidential sessions with you and your key stakeholders, we seek to understand your current processes, your technology, and the specific frustrations you're experiencing day-to-day.
              </span>
            </li>

            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-content-primary">
              <Icon name="ph:number-circle-two" class="w-7 h-7 flex-shrink-0" />

              <span>
                <b class="block">Workflow & Systems Analysis</b>
                We go beyond the surface level, engaging with your team to map out the real-world flow of data and money. We trace the journey from a customer's click to cash in the bank, uncovering the hidden inefficiencies and risks along the way.
              </span>
            </li>

            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-content-primary">
              <Icon name="ph:number-circle-three" class="w-7 h-7 flex-shrink-0" />

              <span>
                <b class="block">The Strategic Roadmap Report</b>
                We compile our findings into a detailed, plain-English report. We document your current state and provide a clear set of prioritised, actionable recommendations for improvement.
              </span>
            </li>

            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-content-primary">
              <Icon name="ph:number-circle-four" class="w-7 h-7 flex-shrink-0" />

              <span>
                <b class="block">The Findings Presentation</b>
                We walk you through our findings and recommendations in a final strategy call. This is an open forum for you and your stakeholders to ask questions, challenge assumptions, and gain complete clarity on the path forward.
              </span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </Fragment>
    </Sectionhead>
  </Container>

  <div class="bg-surface-secondary py-16 my-16">
    <Container>
      <Sectionhead>
        <Fragment slot="title">What You Get: Your Blueprint for Scale</Fragment>
        <Fragment slot="desc">
          <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
            <p class="text-lg text-content-primary mt-4 text-left">This isn't just a report; it's a comprehensive, actionable plan that empowers you to build a finance function that can support your ambition.</p>
            <h2 class="text-content-primary text-lg font-bold mt-8 text-left">1. The Financial Operations Report</h2>
            <p class="text-content-primary text-left">A detailed document providing:</p>
            <ul class="grid mt-4 text-left gap-y-4">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-content-primary">
                <Icon name="ph:check-circle-fill" class="w-6 h-6 flex-shrink-0" />

                <span><b>Payment Bottlenecks:</b> High-volume supplier payment runs are a slow, manual, and painful process</span>
              </li>

              <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-content-primary">
                <Icon name="ph:check-circle-fill" class="w-6 h-6 flex-shrink-0" />

                <span><b>Current State Analysis:</b> A clear summary of your existing financial workflows, systems, and team structure</span>
              </li>

              <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-content-primary">
                <Icon name="ph:check-circle-fill" class="w-6 h-6 flex-shrink-0" />

                <span><b>Bottleneck Identification:</b> Pinpointing the exact areas causing operational drag, risk, and inefficiency</span>
              </li>

              <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-content-primary">
                <Icon name="ph:check-circle-fill" class="w-6 h-6 flex-shrink-0" />

                <span><b>Technology Stack Review:</b> An assessment of your current tools (Xero, Shopify, etc.) and how effectively they are being used</span>
              </li>

              <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-content-primary">
                <Icon name="ph:check-circle-fill" class="w-6 h-6 flex-shrink-0" />

                <span><b>Actionable Recommendations:</b> A prioritised list of strategic and tactical improvements, from "quick wins" to larger foundational projects</span>
              </li>

              <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-content-primary">
                <Icon name="ph:check-circle-fill" class="w-6 h-6 flex-shrink-0" />

                <span><b>Estimated Impact & Effort:</b> A guide to help you understand the potential return and resource requirements for each recommendation</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
            <h2 class="text-content-primary text-lg font-bold mt-8 text-left">2. The Strategy and Q&A Session</h2>
            <p class="text-content-primary text-left">A 90-minute call where we present the report, answer any questions from your team, and ensure you have complete confidence in the recommended path forward.</p>
          </div>
        </Fragment>
      </Sectionhead>
    </Container>
  </div>

  <Container>
    <Sectionhead>
      <Fragment slot="title" class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">Empowered With a Plan,<span class="text-brand-gold-text block mt-1">You're in Control</span></Fragment>
      <Fragment slot="desc">
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          <p class="text-content-primary text-left">The Financial Operations Review delivers a clear, actionable roadmap. To bring this strategic plan to life, you have two straightforward options:</p>
          <ol class="grid mt-4 text-left gap-y-4">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-content-primary">
              <Icon name="ph:number-circle-one" class="w-7 h-7 flex-shrink-0" />

              <span>
                <b class="block">Implement In-House</b>
                Armed with the detailed blueprint from our report, you can guide your internal team to execute the recommended changes at your own pace, using the report as your step-by-step guide.
              </span>
            </li>

            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-content-primary">
              <Icon name="ph:number-circle-two" class="w-7 h-7 flex-shrink-0" />

              <span>
                <b class="block">Partner with Us for Implementation</b>
                Engage us for a separate, fixed-price project. We’ll roll up our sleeves and build the robust, automated systems we’ve designed, ensuring a seamless and expert-led transition for you and your team.
              </span>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </Fragment>
    </Sectionhead>
  </Container>

  <div class="bg-surface-secondary py-16 mt-16 mb-0">
    <Container>
      <Sectionhead>
        <Fragment slot="title">
          <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">A Bespoke Review for Your Unique Business</div>
        </Fragment>
        <Fragment slot="desc">
          <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
            <p class="text-content-primary mt-4 text-left">Every ecommerce business has a unique operational footprint built from its specific mix of sales channels, payment gateways, and inventory systems. To ensure the investment aligns perfectly with the complexity of your business and the value we can deliver, our Financial Operations Review is scoped and priced individually following a brief introductory call.</p>
            <p class="text-content-primary mt-4 text-left">To give you an idea of the investment, here are some typical engagement examples:</p>
            <ul class="grid mt-4 text-left gap-y-4">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-content-primary">
                <Icon name="ph:check-circle-fill" class="w-7 h-7 flex-shrink-0" />

                <span>
                For a UK-based Shopify store with around £1M in turnover using Stripe and PayPal, the investment for a review is typically around £3,500 + VAT
                </span>
              </li>

              <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-content-primary">
                <Icon name="ph:check-circle-fill" class="w-7 h-7 flex-shrink-0" />

                <span>
                For a multi-channel retailer with £3M in turnover, selling in the UK and EU with inventory complexity, the investment is typically around £5,500 + VAT
                </span>
              </li>

              <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-content-primary">
                <Icon name="ph:check-circle-fill" class="w-7 h-7 flex-shrink-0" />

                <span>
                For a larger £5M+ business with international sales, multiple currencies, and wholesale/D2C arms, the investment typically starts from £7,500 + VAT
                </span>
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-content-primary mt-4 text-left">The next step is a no-obligation scoping call. We’ll ask some targeted questions about your operations to understand your specific needs. This allows us to provide a firm, fixed-fee quote for you to consider, with no obligation to proceed.</p>
          </div>
        </Fragment>
      </Sectionhead>
    </Container>
  </div>

  <Cta />
</Layout>
